      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected based on turbulence model sensitivity study (VR-05) and published recommendations for rotating blood-contacting devices. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis correlation selected as the most widely validated correlation for CFD hemolysis prediction in centrifugal pumps. The correlation is derived under the theoretical precondition that scalar stress exposure accumulates linearly along fluid pathlines — a condition the model narrative describes as broadly applicable to turbomachinery flows. This precondition is accepted without dedicated verification for the COU operating regime."
